 the southernmost portion of Blind Island to the hunting closure markers one mile south of the Blind Slough bridge, are closed to all hunting. (iii) Unit-specific regulations; (A) Bait may be used to hunt black bear between April 15 and June 15; (B) Boats may not be used to take ungulates, bear, wolves, or wolverine, except for persons certified as disabled.
